name: Prayers to Maalik The Ruler Over All
description: Marking the end of summer, early November is brought by a cool breeze towards the gates of the rainy season. The 'Maalik' harvest festival by making a large dish that has its own meaning such as yellow rice (a form of gratitude to God), rainbow crackers (celebrating diversity), vegetables (respecting nature), 3 color dumplings (symbol of the cycle of life), satay meat (strength), fish satay (humble) that resembles a row of trees.
